How to run the fetch_tool playbook?

$ cd ansible/prod_install

//The version variable specifies the checkout clone output directory
//dir_name: Name of the directory in which the tool will be install (find the full path in your Ansible variable file), e.g. develop
//username: Change user name! Must be your organisation linux username, e.g. maxim
//version: The name of the branch or tag version you want to check out, e.g. develop OR v4.0.5
//tagged_version: Type true if you want to checkout/pull a tagged version or false if you want to checkout/pull a feature branch
//env: Type dev if you you want to install the tool under the test-clones directory or prod if you want to install a new production clone

$ ansible-playbook -vvv -i prod-inventory playbooks/install.yml --extra-vars "dir_name=v2.0 user=maxim version=web-updater-v2.0 tagged_version=true env=dev" --ask-pass --tags "new_version"

Additional useful information:

How to add the Conda Ansible Module (https://github.com/UDST/ansible-conda)?

1. Change the Ansible configuration and set library variable

    $ nano /etc/ansible/ansible.cfg

    library        = /usr/share/ansible

2. Download Conda module and unzip it in the library directory

    # You might have to do all those tasks as super user
    $ cd /usr/share/ansible

    $ wget -O ansible-conda-master.zip https://github.com/UDST/ansible-conda/archive/master.zip

    $ unzip ansible-conda-master.zip

3. Check if Conda module is in the list of install Ansible modules

    $ ansible-doc -l